 with unity within uncertainty. The rates at each distance were found\nto be similar, but 20-24\\% lower than expected, thus reaffirming the anomaly.\nThese results are consistent with $\\nu_e \\rightarrow \\nu_s$ oscillations with a\nrelatively large $\\Delta m^2$ ($>$0.5 eV$^2$) and mixing sin$^2 2\\theta$\n($\\approx$0.4).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 23 Sep 2021 16:35:51 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 30 Mar 2022 17:42:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-22"}
