tly weaker than that estimated in\nthe optical at previous epochs. Finally, we measured the radial velocity of the\nstar and filtered out the stellar activity jitter using both ZDI and Gaussian\nProcess Regression down to a precision of ~0.15 and 0.08 $\\mathrm{km\\,s^{-1}}$\nRMS, respectively, confirming the previously published upper limit on the mass\nof a potential close-in massive planet around V410 Tau.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 24 Sep 2021 05:54:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-10-05"}
